description.narrative: Social care programmes at national and local level address identified vulnerabilities of disadvantaged children and families, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Reducing Child Poverty, Social Protection And Child Poverty. title.narrative: Social care programmes at national and local level address identified vulnerabilities of disadvantaged children and families

description.narrative: The economic and social vulnerabilities of 11,023 children with severe mental and/or physical disabilities and their families were addressed through the provision of regular cash transfers and case management services in five governorates. In addition, major progress was made during the year to strengthen the quality of the Integrated Social Protection Programme for Children with Disabilities, including the extension of benefits from 12 to 24 months; expansion of eligibility criteria; establishment of a consolidated registry; and establishment of a centralized grievance mechanisms. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:16/01/2022
